he Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The guidelines require transgender women to have transitioned before the age of 12 to be eligible for the women's category, to prevent any potential biological advantage from male puberty.\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1493, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The guidelines\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1319}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender women\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1345}, {\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's category\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1427}, {\"ngram\": \"any potential biological advantage\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1474}, {\"ngram\": \"male puberty\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1492}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Which sports have these rules?\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1525, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Which sports\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1507}, {\"ngram\": \"these rules\", \"from\": 1513, \"to\": 1524}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The guidelines from the IOC have been adopted by World Athletics and Fina, swimming's governing body.\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1551, \"end\": 1554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.564949574546304e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1576, \"end\": 1591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.667346449504459e-22, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The guidelines\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"Fina\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1600}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming's governing body\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1627}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cycling follow these guidelines for women's categories but also allow for an \\\"open\\\" category which has replaced the current \\\"men's category\\\" to allow transgender athletes to compete.\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1812, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cycling\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"these guidelines\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"women's categories\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"an \\\"open\\\" category\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1722}, {\"ngram\": \"the current \\\"men's category\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender athletes\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1800}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Rowing allows those who transitioned before puberty to be eligible, and one of their criteria is for the testosterone concentration to be less than 2.5 nmol/L for a period of at least 24 months, while rugby has followed the IOC guidelines.\", \"from\": 1814, \"to\": 2059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2044, \"end\": 2047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.564949574546304e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Rowing\", \"from\": 1814, \"to\": 1826}, {\"ngram\": \"puberty\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"their criteria\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1913}, {\"ngram\": \"the testosterone concentration\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 1951}, {\"ngram\": \"less than 2.5 nmol/L\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"a period\", \"from\": 1983, \"to\": 1991}, {\"ngram\": \"at least 24 months\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2013}, {\"ngram\": \"rugby\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2026}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Triathlon, tennis and 